<td valign="top" style="padding-right:30px; padding-left:20px;">
<div id="Idea_4326"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaTitle">
<a href="/akira/dtd/4326-4049"><span id="IdeaTitle_4326">MyPersonalGovernment.gov (MPG Program; Making Government work for its citizens)&nbsp;</span></a>
</div>
<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/4808-4049">Sam Mehrani</a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">4 hours ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">---- PART I ---- ORIGIN<br/><br/>1. UNITY FOR SOLVING COMPLICATIONS<br/><br/>“The state or quality of being one; singleness.”<br/><br/>“The state or quality of being in accord; harmony.”<br/><br/>“The combination or arrangement of parts into a whole; unification.”<br/><br/>“A combination or union thus formed.”<br/><br/>“Singleness or constancy of purpose or action; continuity.”<br/><br/>“An ordering of all elements in a work of art or literature so that each contributes to a unified aesthetic effect. The effect thus produced.”<br/><br/>“The state of being one”<br/><br/>“Mutual agreement: unity of intention”<br/><br/>“The state of being a single thing that is composed of separate parts, organizations, etc.”<br/><br/>“Mathematics: The number 1.”<br/><br/><br/>---- PART II ---- THOUGTS<br/><br/>THOUGT 1: FIND COMMON DENOMINATOR TO UNITE<br/><br/>“Common denominator: An attribute that is common to all members of a category.”<br/><br/>1.1. Assumption<br/>A common denominator can unite members of a category because it’s common to all members of a category.<br/><br/>1.2. Argument<br/>The category is the US, which consists of three dominant attributes known as Democracy, Capitalism and Religion. These dominant attributes are not common to all its members referred to as citizens.<br/><br/>1.3. Statement<br/>Democracy can be the political orientation of those who favor government by the people or by their elected representatives or a political system in which the supreme power lies in a body of citizens who can elect people to represent them or majority rule: the doctrine that the numerical majority of an organized group can make decisions binding on the whole group. Capitalism is an economic system based on private ownership of capital. Religion can be a strong belief in a supernatural power or powers that control human destiny or an institution to express belief in a divine power.<br/>Current situation of dominant attributes: Democracy is imperfect because the distribution of power leaves some or the majority of its citizens without power. Capitalism is imperfect because the distribution of capital leaves some or the majority without capital. Religion is imperfect because it’s fractioned (Fraction: a component of a mixture that has been separated by a fractional process).<br/><br/>The common denominator can in theory consist of one attribute but in reality is often a complex system of attributes, depending on the complexity of the category. The current dominant attributes are not functioning as the common denominator, which leaves the members (US citizens) of a category (The US) not united.<br/><br/>1.4. Proposal<br/>Complete current set of dominant attributes with new dominant attribute: Individualism.<br/><br/>Individualism contradicts collectiveness and thus unity, but in the complex set of (dominant) attributes it is the unorthodox solution to unity because it transcends the current flaws of the current dominant attributes. Individualism leaves members that lack capital, power and belief with greater human capital, individual power and solves fragmentation (fragmentation: the disintegration of social norms governing behavior and thought and social relationships).<br/><br/>THOUGHT 2: RETHINK GLOBALIZATION FOR ITS OBJECTIVE<br/><br/>“Globalization: Growth to a global or worldwide scale. Globalization in its literal sense is the process of transformation of local or regional phenomena into global ones. It can be described as a process by which the people of the world are unified into a single society and function together.”<br/><br/>2.1. Assumption<br/>Rethinking globalization can significantly improve the feasibility of the objective of globalization.<br/><br/>2.2. Argument<br/>Integral process segments of globalization contradict with its objective of a unified world with a single society that functions together.<br/><br/>2.3. Statement<br/>Without a common denominator for a category defined on a global scale, the objective of globalization can’t be maintained. The attribute Individualism is marginalized due to integral process segments that rely far more on the current dominant attributes, Democracy, Capitalism and Religion.<br/><br/>2.4. Proposal<br/>Complete current set of dominant attributes with new dominant attribute: Individualism.<br/><br/>Individualism contradicts collectiveness and thus unity, but in the complex set of (dominant) attributes it is the unorthodox solution to unity because it transcends the current flaws of the current dominant attributes. Individualism leaves members that lack capital, power and belief with greater human capital, individual power and solves fragmentation (fragmentation: the disintegration of social norms governing behavior and thought and social relationships). Individualism as a dominant attribute will create a balance between all the dominant attributes and therefore increase the feasibility of the objective of globalization.<br/><br/>THOUGHT 3: REDEFINE GOVERNMENT FOR UNITY OF ITS CITIZENS<br/><br/>“Government: The organization that is the governing authority of a political unit or the act of governing or government: The system or form by which a community or other political unit is governed.”<br/><br/>3.1. Assumption<br/>Redefining government with a balanced set of dominant attributes can create a common denominator that unites its citizens.<br/><br/>3.2. Argument<br/>Integral process segments of government are not sustainable.<br/><br/>3.3. Statement<br/>Without the dominant attribute Individualism the Common denominator doesn’t function.<br/><br/>3.4. Proposal<br/>Complete current set of dominant attributes with new dominant attribute: Individualism.<br/><br/>Individualism contradicts collectiveness and thus unity, but in the complex set of (dominant) attributes it is the unorthodox solution to unity because it transcends the current flaws of the current dominant attributes. Individualism leaves members that lack capital, power and belief with greater human capital, individual power and solves fragmentation (fragmentation: the disintegration of social norms governing behavior and thought and social relationships). Implementation of the dominant attribute Individualism in integral process segments will benefit government and its citizens.<br/><br/><br/>---- PART III ---- SUGGESTIONS<br/><br/>SUGGESTION 1: TRANSFORM ABSTRACT DOMINANT ATTRIBUTE INDIVIDUALISM TO REFORM POLICY<br/><br/>1.1. Explanation<br/>The current dominant attributes Democracy, Capitalism and Religion are integral parts of the System (System: Includes all formal and informal practices and procedures). The dominant attribute Individualism is a marginal part of the system and needs to be implemented as an integral part of the system.<br/><br/>1.2. Recommendation<br/>Review all procedures on the absence of the dominant attribute Individualism and implement the dominant attribute with the objective to build sustainable human capital & individual power for members (citizens) of a category (the US).<br/><br/>SUGGESTION 2: DECREASE FLAWS DOMINANT ATTRIBUTES DEMOCRACY, CAPITALISM & RELIGION<br/><br/>2.1. Explanation<br/>The current dominant attributes Democracy, Capitalism and Religion are integral parts of the System (System: Includes all formal and informal practices and procedures). The current dominant attributes flaws in regards to unity should be contained in reversed policy.<br/><br/>2.2. Recommendation<br/>Review all procedures on the presence of flaws of the dominant attributes Democracy, Capitalism and Religion with the objective to integrate social norms governing behavior and thought and social relationships. The interpretation of flaws should depend on their usability to enhance unity.<br/><br/><br/>---- PART IV ---- IDEAS<br/><br/>IDEA 1: FROM GOVERNING-BASED GOVERNMENT ORGANIZATION TO SERVICE-BASED GOVERNMENT ORGANIZATION<br/><br/>IDEA 2: EMPOWERMENT BY MARGINALIZED PEOPLE TO EMPOWERMENT BY PROCESS ACCESSIBILITY & PARTICIPATION<br/><br/>IDEA 3: FROM MISPLACED CULTURAL & NATIONAL IDENTITY TO A SOLID PERSONAL IDENTITY<br/><br/>IDEA 4: FROM HOLISTIC COLLECTIVISIM TO CONNECTING INDIVIDUALISM<br/><br/>IDEA 5: HOLISTIC CLOSED CHANGE VS. OPEN CHANGE MANAGEMENT PROCESS<br/><br/>IDEA 6: FROM COLLECTIVIST POLITICAL THEORIES TO INDIVIDUALIST THEORY IN GOVERNMENT<br/><br/>IDEA 7: FROM THE POWER OF A FEW TO THE POWER OF ONE<br/><br/><br/>---- PART V ---- APPLICATION MPG PROGRAM<br/><br/>1. MY PERSONAL GOVERNMENT PROGRAM (MPG PROGRAM)<br/><br/>“Making Government work for its citizens.”<br/><br/>1.1. What is the MPG Program?<br/>A systematic approach towards unity, on every level, by endorsing Individualism.<br/><br/>1.2. How does it work?<br/>It emphasizes all the current flaws of “the system” because it contradicts the dogmas. (Dogma: An authoritative principle, belief, or statement of ideas or opinion, especially one considered to be absolutely true.)<br/><br/>1.3 How and where do you start with the MPG program?<br/>On a personal (individual) level it is difficult, because a person’s ability to find all his/her personal dogmas is not supported by “the system”. Simply put, the resources are not (yet) made available.<br/><br/>On a local or regional level it is much easier, because “the system” can then provide a person the necessary resources to understand his/her dogmas and work on them to find individuality and ultimately unity.<br/><br/>Preferred is a global (universal) “system” change that provides the necessary resources to find ones dogmas and work on them to find individuality and ultimately unity.<br/><br/>1.4 What should the US government do to make this possible?<br/>Start with it self because it has the resources to find its dogmas. If it finds its dogmas, comprehends its dogmas and utilizes its capability? Government can and then will implement the process for all.</div>
